<PERSON> Ruby </PERSON> on `` General Hospital.'' `` They make our days long and hard. They're illiterate,'' she said Wednesday as she walked a picket line with the guild. `` You have to continue,'' said <PERSON> Jerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Balme </PERSON>, one of the show's producers `` You owe it to the audience and to the network,'' he said, adding: `` We miss -LRB- the writers -RRB-. We want them back.'' The writing is `` getting to look like ` See <PERSON> Dick </PERSON> run,''' said actress <PERSON> Peggy </PERSON> <PERSON> McCary </PERSON> of `` Days of Our Lives.'' Labor-management relations can be unusual in <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION>. Striking scriptwriter <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Goethals </PERSON> said he is surviving on tuna fish sandwiches and loans from friends, who also happen to be producers. Producer <PERSON> Cannell </PERSON>, also a member of the <ORGANIZATION> Writers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guild </ORGANIZATION>, honors the strike and stays away from his typewriter. `` Since I was a writer first, I'm not going to scab during the strike,'' <PERSON> Cannell </PERSON> said. But he feels a conflict. `` I do n't think it's going to settle on the Writers Guild terms no matter what they think. I think it could go on to January if the wrong set of philosophies get used ... if they keep saying the companies are getting fat.'' Like many other producers, <PERSON> Cannell </PERSON> has cut paychecks in half as a means of keeping on staff. <ORGANIZATION> Cannell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Productions </ORGANIZATION> turns out such television series as `` Hunter,'' `` The A-Team,'' `` <ORGANIZATION> Hardcastle </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> McCormick </PERSON>'' and `` The Rockford Files.'' Meanwhile, `` Moonlighting'' star <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> <PERSON> Willis </PERSON> has taken up gardening. His ABC-TV series shut down early because of a lack of scripts. Though he's not at work, <PERSON> Willis </PERSON> still has his problems. `` I'm having a lot of trouble with snails,'' <PERSON> Willis </PERSON> said recently as he surveyed a tiny bed of marigolds and snapdragons.
