<HEAD>No Warning For Tornado That Killed Two</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SCOTT SONNER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>GRETNA, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An unusual late-night tornado slammed into a mobile home without warning, killing a woman and her baby and critically injuring her husband while thunderstorms caused scattered damage in eastern <LOCATION> Nebraska </LOCATION>. Two-inch hailstones broke windows in <LOCATION> Omaha </LOCATION> and wind up to 60 mph pushed over trees and damaged other mobile homes. The tornado touched down with no warning, ripping the roof off a farmhouse and causing extensive damage to another house as well as the mobile home shortly before 11 p.m. Saturday, said <LOCATION> Sarpy </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> Chief Deputy <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Polikov </PERSON>. `` The weather service is not feeling too good about not being able to get a warning out before,'' <PERSON> Polikov </PERSON> said Sunday. `` It is unusual to have them that late at night in this area. They usually are in the evening. It could n't be seen by radar.'' <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Byrd </PERSON>, a meteorologist for the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Weather </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Omaha </LOCATION>, said Sunday that the tornado touched down only for a few minutes. He confirmed the funnel was not detected by radar. `` It was the same thunderstorm that we followed with 1-inch hail in the <LOCATION> Lincoln </LOCATION> area, but as far as showing a tornado, that was n't apparent through our radar detector,'' he said `` We started detecting it in western <LOCATION> Douglas </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, but that was after it had touched down. It apparently touched down and then went right back up.'' Small tornadoes that touch down only briefly are much more difficult to detect than large ones, <PERSON> Byrd </PERSON> said. Two-year-old <PERSON> Lynn </PERSON> <PERSON> True </PERSON> was dead at the scene, <PERSON> Polikov </PERSON> said. Her mother, <PERSON> Joan </PERSON> <PERSON> True </PERSON>, 29, died o